      rationale: "Research-phase concern, not Clarify-phase. Ticket 118 is complete; the canonical install URL is determined by 118's deployment and is a fact research will confirm. The intent — wrap the curl bootstrap installer — is unambiguous regardless of which URL 118 ultimately published."
    - finding_index: 1
      rationale: "The source explicitly says the formula is a 'thin wrapper' that 'doesn't own ~/.claude/ deployment, it just runs the curl script once and prints caveats.' That is the architectural answer to what brew owns. Specifics like Cellar contents and brew uninstall semantics are research-phase investigation, not Clarify-phase intent ambiguity."
    - finding_index: 2
      rationale: "Misreads DR-5 architectural split. DR-5 separates 'install the tool' (curl/brew/uv handle this) from 'deploy ~/.claude/' (cortex setup handles this). The curl script from ticket 118 installs the cortex CLI via `uv tool install` and does not touch ~/.claude/. The post_install hazard the source flags was specifically about formulas writing to user config; brew upgrade re-running an idempotent CLI installer is not the same hazard."
    - finding_index: 4
      rationale: "Items flagged (tap repo owner, pin vs latest, brew audit style, version string) are research-phase fact-finding to be resolved by reading code/docs, not architectural design trade-offs requiring user judgment. The lifecycle's Research→Specify automatic complexity-escalation gate (≥2 open questions in research.md) will catch any genuine complexity surfaced by research."
    - finding_index: 5
      rationale: "Same DR-5 reasoning as finding 2: curl script does not deploy ~/.claude/. brew upgrade re-running it re-installs the CLI idempotently via `uv tool install`. The blast-radius hazard the critic describes is mitigated architecturally; medium criticality stands."
